OL,3,CIs Badenoch right to propose the end
OL,4,Cof stamp duty?
OL,6,FThe reform package would be revenue-
OL,7,Fneutral in the longer term, but very
OL,8,Fexpensive in the first few years
OL,9,F(because the new property wealth tax
OL,10,Fcould only be phased in). So the
OL,11,Freform is probably not affordable for
OL,12,FReeves in her forthcoming November
OL,13,Fbudget, given she has to fill a #30bn
OL,14,Fblack hole.
OL,16,FBy definition, the abolition would be
OL,17,Feven less affordable for a Tory
OL,18,Fgovernment that isn't proposing to
OL,19,Fraise an equivalent sum from an annual
OL,20,Fcharge on housing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
