OL,3,CIs Badenoch right to propose the end
OL,4,Cof stamp duty?
OL,6,FBut Badenoch is postulating #47bn of
OL,7,Fspending cuts - to welfare, overseas
OL,8,Faid, social housing and so on - and
OL,9,Fperhaps some of these cuts would be
OL,10,Fpractical and deliverable.
OL,12,FAlso, she has at least four years, and
OL,13,Fmaybe an eternity, before she has the
OL,14,Fpower to do anything in government.
OL,16,FBadenoch has, however, done a public
OL,17,Fservice in putting stamp duty
OL,18,Fabolition firmly on the political
OL,19,Fagenda. My hunch is that, one way or
OL,20,Fanother, the days are numbered for
OL,21,Fthis toxic tax.
